abstract: HOUSTON, Oct. 12--In three other National League championship series, the Philadelphia Phillies lost. And tonight they had the opportunity to surrender when the Houston Astros took a 5-2 lead in the seventh inning. But after the Phillies won the pennant with an 8-7 victory in 10 innings, Pete Rose had the best explanation.
headline_main: Phils Were 'Just Tired of Losing'; No Haunting Memories Ruthven Was Set for Long Relief

abstract: HOUSTON, Oct. 12--In the fourth straight extra-inning game of a tumultuous playoff, the Philadelphia Phillies rallied in the eighth and 10th innings tonight to defeat the Houston Astros, 8-7, and win their first National League pennant in 30 years.

abstract: Wyoming Seminary, which had its winning streak snapped at 31 games last week when it was tied by Blair, lost yesterday for the first time in five years when Canterbury edged the Pennsylvania football team, 7-0. Scott Chamness's 60-yard run on the second play from scrimmage gave the undefeated home team its fourth victory.

abstract: HOUSTON, Oct. 11--For all the disputes over umpires' decisions in the Philadelphia Phillies' bizarre 5-3 victory today that created a decisive fifth playoff game tomorrow night for the National League pennant, an undisputed appeal that Gary Woods of the Houston Astros had left third base too soon on a sacrifice fly turned out to be the most important.
